根据阿勒颇历史学家 Kamel Al-Ghazzi 的记载，在19世纪初，阿勒颇的人口约40万。19世纪阿勒颇的经济衰落，以及19世纪上半叶的地震、瘟疫，使得19世纪末阿勒颇人口减少至11万<ref>Saint Terezia Church Aleppo [http://www.terezia.org/section.php?id=1823 Christians in Aleppo at the end of the Ottoman Empire] {{Wayback|url=http://www.terezia.org/section.php?id=1823 |date=20171009230825 }}</ref><ref>Suraiya Faroqhi, Halil İnalcık, Donald Quataert (1997). "''[https://books.google.com/books?id=c00jmTrjzAoC&pg=PA788&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false An economic and social history of the Ottoman Empire] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=c00jmTrjzAoC&pg=PA788&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false |date=20200917214659 }}''". Cambridge University Press. 788. ISBN 0-521-57455-2</ref>。1901年，阿勒颇有人口108,143，其中穆斯林76,329 (70.58%)，基督徒24,508 (22.66%)，犹太人7,306 (6.76%)<ref>Alepppo in One Hundred Years 1850– 1950, vol.2-page 3, 1994 Aleppo. Authors: Mohammad Fuad Ayntabi and Najwa Othman</ref>。

[[亚美尼亚大屠杀|亚美尼亚大屠杀]]后，大量亚美尼亚和[[亚述人|亚述]]难民涌入阿勒颇。1922年，阿勒颇有人口156,748，其中穆斯林97,600 (62.26%)，本地基督徒22,117 (14.11%)，亚美尼亚人20,007 (12.76%)，犹太人6,580 (4.20%)，欧洲人2,652 (1.70%)，其他7,792 (4.97%)<ref>Alepppo in One Hundred Years 1850–1950, vol.3-page 26, 1994 Aleppo. Authors: Mohammad Fuad Ayntabi and Najwa Othman</ref><ref>The Golden River in the History of Aleppo, ({{lang-ar|ﻧﻬﺮ ﺍﻟﺬﻫﺐ ﻓﻲ ﺗﺎﺭﻳﺦ ﺣﻠﺐ}}), vol.1 (1922) page 256, published in 1991, Aleppo. Author: Sheikh ''Kamel Al-Ghazzi''</ref>。1923年法国撤出[[奇里乞亚|奇里乞亚]]后，阿勒颇出现了第二波亚美尼亚人移民潮<ref>The Golden River in the History of Aleppo ({{lang-ar|ﻧﻬﺮ ﺍﻟﺬﻫﺐ ﻓﻲ ﺗﺎﺭﻳﺦ ﺣﻠﺐ}}), vol.3 (1925) pages 449–450, published in 1991, Aleppo. Author: Sheikh ''Kamel Al-Ghazzi''</ref>。1944年，阿勒颇人口达到325,000，其中基督徒112,110(34.5%) ，其中亚美尼亚人60,200。1946-1967年间，亚美尼亚人很多移民往苏联。据估计，内战前阿勒颇仍留有60,000亚美尼亚人<ref name="Arm. Min. Diaspora">{{cite web |url=http://www.armdiasporamuseum.com/227-1-page.html |title=The Virtual Museum of Armenian Diaspora |publisher=Ministry of Diaspora of the Republic of Armenia |date= |accessdate=2014-02-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20140219123645/http://www.armdiasporamuseum.com/227-1-page.html |archivedate=2014-02-19 }}</ref>。

据2004年叙利亚中央统计局数据，阿勒颇人口为2,132,100<ref name="CBS">{{cite web|url=http://www.cbssyr.org/new%20web%20site/General_census/census_2004/NH/TAB02-1-2004.htm |title=General Census of Population and Housing 2004 |accessdate=2012-05-20|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120520173518/http://www.cbssyr.org/new%20web%20site/General_census/census_2004/NH/TAB02-1-2004.htm |archivedate=20 May 2012 }}Syria Central Bureau of Statistics. Aleppo Governorate. {{ar icon}}</ref>。阿勒颇居民绝大多数为[[阿拉伯人|阿拉伯人]]，使用[[黎凡特阿拉伯语|黎凡特阿拉伯语]]阿勒颇方言。

== 经济 ==
在历史上，阿勒颇长期是中东重要的商业城市。阿勒颇向东是通向巴格达、摩苏尔以及印度、伊朗的商路，向西是安纳托利亚和君士坦丁堡，向南则是大马士革。在欧洲人使用经好望角的航线，以至后来开辟苏伊士运河之前，阿勒颇也在欧洲与东方的贸易中发挥巨大的作用。在奥斯曼时代，阿勒颇的发达程度仅次于君士坦丁堡及开罗<ref name="otm-enc"/>。

叙利亚独立后，阿勒颇是叙利亚的工业和经济中心<ref name=BBCprofile></ref>。现代阿勒颇的主要产业包括纺织、化工、矿冶、制药、农业加工、电子、机械工业和旅游业。阿勒颇的制造业在叙利亚全国有支柱性的地位，其制造业工人数量在全国占比接近50%<ref>Madinatuna: Aleppo City Development Strategy [http://madinatuna.com/en/economy Economy] {{Wayback|url=http://madinatuna.com/en/economy |date=20100505211720 }}</ref>。阿勒颇的经济以制造业为主导。据官方统计数据，全市劳动人口中，产业工人占60.2%，30.5%是工业工人，其中绝大多数为制造业工人，两项数值均远高于大马士革（分别为38.1%和18.0%）<ref>{{cite web|author1=Syria Central Bureau of Statistics|title=توزع المشتغلين(15 سنة فأكثر) حسب أقسام النشاط الإقتصادي الرئيسي والمحافظات والجنس ( حضر  - ريف )|url=http://www.cbssyr.sy/work/2010/ALL-2010/TAB13.htm|accessdate=2016-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221083154/http://www.cbssyr.sy/work/2010/ALL-2010/TAB13.htm|archive-date=2016-12-21|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="GIZ">{{cite book|author1=Aleppo Urban Development Project|title=Report on Local Economic Development in Aleppo|date=2010|url=http://www2.giz.de/wbf/4tDx9kw63gma/Rabenau_LED.pdf|accessdate=2016-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021030627/http://www2.giz.de/wbf/4tDx9kw63gma/Rabenau_LED.pdf|archive-date=2016-10-21|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。此外，阿勒颇的经济与土耳其联系紧密，当地80%以上的工厂从土耳其进口原材料<ref name="SEF">{{cite book|author1=Syrian Economic Forum|title=Economics of Aleppo|date=2015|url=http://www.syrianef.org/En/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/aleppo-report-final.pdf|accessdate=2016-12-03|archive-date=2020-09-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200917214540/http://www.syrianef.org/En/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/aleppo-report-final.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。阿勒颇主要的工业区，{{le|谢赫·纳贾尔工业城|Sheikh Najjar}}，位于市区东北，是叙利亚最大的工业区之一，占地面积4,412公顷，投资34亿美元，有约1900家企业进驻<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aksalser.com/?page=view_news&id=5ace559cb86c8b34f1e024e479b11815&ar=17773089 |title=155 billion Syrian Pounds invested in Aleppo Industrial City |publisher=Aksalser.com |accessdate=11 March 2012 |archive-date=2012-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120303110557/http://www.aksalser.com/?page=view_news&id=5ace559cb86c8b34f1e024e479b11815&ar=17773089 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 主要产业 ===

纺织业是阿勒颇的支柱性产业之一。在奥斯曼帝国时期，阿勒颇商人的主要贸易活动之一就是从波斯等地进口棉花、羊毛和丝绸，加工后再销往奥斯曼帝国各地和欧洲。纺织业的兴衰与阿勒颇的经济地位密切相关<ref name="otm-enc"/>。阿勒颇的现代纺织工业起源于法国托管时期，当时外来资本多集中于资源开采和基础设施。而面向本地市场的纺织业，则在传统纺织业的基础上不受干扰地迅速发展，并机械化<ref>{{cite book|author1=Geoffrey D. Schad|title=''France, Syrie et Liban, 1918-1946''|date=2002|publisher=Presses de l’Ifpo, Institut français d'études arabes de Damas|location=Damas|isbn=9782901315773|pages=291-312}}</ref>。在阿勒颇省，纺织业提供的就业岗位占工业总数的37.9%。在阿勒颇主要的工业区谢赫·纳贾尔工业城，纺织业占有54.1%的投资和42.8％的就业岗位。目前，阿勒颇拥有叙利亚全国35%的纺织企业，产值和工人数量的占比与之相似<ref name="GIZ"/>。

依据官方数据，包含化工、制药和部分传统手工艺品制作（例如著名的阿勒颇手工皂、化妆品、香水等）在内的化工类工业提供了21.2%的工业就业岗位。叙利亚对外国石化产品的进口有严格的限制，因此集中于阿勒颇附近的叙利亚石化企业在本土面临的竞争较小。约40%的石化产品用于出口，主要目的地是伊拉克和东欧<ref name="GIZ"/>。叙利亚的制药业在20世纪80年代开始兴起，在2010年，叙利亚有制药企业约70家，可满足国内91%的需求<ref>{{cite news|author1=Lysandra Ohrstrom|title=Syria war wreaks havoc on drug industry|url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/Business/Middle-East/2013/Jul-01/222083-syria-war-wreaks-havoc-on-drug-industry.ashx|accessdate=2016-12-03|agency=The Daily Star|date=2013-07-01|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112015303/http://www.dailystar.com.lb/Business/Middle-East/2013/Jul-01/222083-syria-war-wreaks-havoc-on-drug-industry.ashx|dead-url=no}}</ref>。约40%的叙利亚制药企业位于阿勒颇<ref name="GIZ"/><ref>{{cite book|author1=Abdullah Hamada|title=''The Syrian crisis: Repercussions of the pharmaceutical industry.''|date=2014|publisher=Syrian Economic Forum|url=http://www.syrianef.org/En/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Pharmaceutical-Industry-en.pdf|access-date=2016-12-03|archive-date=2020-09-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200917224821/http://www.syrianef.org/En/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Pharmaceutical-Industry-en.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

以阿勒颇为中心的阿勒颇省西北部有叙利亚最肥沃的农业区之一，主要农作物为大麦、小麦、鹰嘴豆和棉花<ref name="GIZ"/>。2010年，阿勒颇省有118万公顷耕地，小麦产量占全国20%<ref>{{cite web|author1=Syrian State Bureau of Statistics|title=استعمالات الأراضي حسب المحافظة 2010(ألف هكتار )|url=http://www.cbssyr.sy/yearbook/2011/Data-Chapter4/TAB-7-4-2011.htm|accessdate=2016-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305025806/http://www.cbssyr.sy/yearbook/2011/Data-Chapter4/TAB-7-4-2011.htm|archive-date=2017-03-05|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="SNAP"></ref>。以此为基础，阿勒颇市内发展起了规模较大的农业加工产业。阿勒颇有约3600家农产品加工企业，其中约1/3有规模化生产的能力，其余为手工作坊性质。农产品加工行业提供了阿勒颇工业方面就业岗位的11.5%<ref name="GIZ"/>。

旅游业和手工业也是阿勒颇经济的重要组成成分。2007年，阿勒颇接受外国游客600万人次。其中，非阿拉伯国家游客占21.2%，以土耳其和伊朗游客为主；每100名居民对应的游客人数平均为9.1人，排在大马士革、拉塔基亚和塔尔图斯之后<ref name="GIZ"/>。

=== 内战影响 ===

2012年以来，阿勒颇的经济遭到严重破坏。内战开始后，谢赫·纳贾尔工业区位于交战区附近，在2014年重新由政府军控制之前，曾一度近于完全废弃<ref>{{cite news|author1=Robert Fisk|title=Aleppo's Sheikh Najjar: The death of a once-rich city|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/aleppos-sheikh-najjar-the-death-of-a-once-rich-city-9503699.html|accessdate=2016-11-03|publisher=Independent|date=2014-06-06|archive-date=2016-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104075537/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/aleppos-sheikh-najjar-the-death-of-a-once-rich-city-9503699.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=War-ravaged Syrian industrial zone hopes for new life|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-2842436/War-ravaged-Syrian-industrial-zone-hopes-new-life.html|accessdate=2016-11-03|agency=AFP|publisher=Dailymail|date=2014-11-20|archive-date=2017-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305131105/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-2842436/War-ravaged-Syrian-industrial-zone-hopes-new-life.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在反对派控制期间，这里的许多工厂被拆解后卖往土耳其<ref>{{cite news|author1=Fehim Taştekin|title=Return to Aleppo: A squandered legacy|url=http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2017/01/turkey-syria-return-to-aleppo-squandering-legacy.html|accessdate=2017-01-15|agency=Al-Monitor|date=2017-01-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170114193338/http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2017/01/turkey-syria-return-to-aleppo-squandering-legacy.html|archive-date=2017-01-14|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。阿勒颇北部另一个规模稍小的工业区莱拉蒙（Layramoun，{{lang-ar|البلليرمون}}），含有约1200座工厂，近期也遭到洗劫<ref>{{cite news|author1=Barak Barfi|title=''In Aleppo, I Saw Why Assad Is Winning''|url=http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2016/12/aleppo-syria-assad-214494|accessdate=2016-12-05|agency=Politico|date=2016-12-02|archive-date=2021-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210516192315/https://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2016/12/aleppo-syria-assad-214494|dead-url=no}}</ref>。依据当地政府2016年统计，阿勒颇目前的工业产值约为内战开始前的10%<ref>{{cite news|author1=Nabih Bulos|title=Aleppo was Syria's factory floor. Now it's in ruins and business leaders wonder if it's safe to rebuild|url=http://www.latimes.com/world/middleeast/la-fg-syria-aleppo-economy-20161113-story.html|accessdate=2016-12-05|agency=LA Times|date=2016-11-15|archive-date=2021-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226120426/https://www.latimes.com/world/middleeast/la-fg-syria-aleppo-economy-20161113-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。叙利亚北部许多地区处于无政府状态，因此其工业生产还深受高犯罪率的影响。从阿勒颇向东运送的货物经常遭到抢劫，以致许多企业愿意承担高出数倍的运费，将出口往伊拉克的产品先运往黎巴嫩，从那里经海路运往目的地<ref>{{cite news|title=Crime Wave Engulfs Syria as Its Cities Reel From War|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/10/world/middleeast/crime-wave-engulfs-syria-as-its-cities-reel-from-war.html|accessdate=2016-12-05|agency=The New York Times|date=2012-08-09|archive-date=2021-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210503095820/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/10/world/middleeast/crime-wave-engulfs-syria-as-its-cities-reel-from-war.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。很多仍在运营的工厂已经迁往拉塔基亚、塔尔图斯和霍姆斯，或约旦等国<ref>{{cite news|author1=Younes Ahmed|title=Syrian factories relocating to coastal area|url=http://www.thearabweekly.com/Opinion/887/Syrian-factories-relocating-to-coastal-area|accessdate=2016-12-05|agency=The Arab Weekly|date=2015-06-26|archive-date=2017-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170306033924/http://www.thearabweekly.com//opinion/887/Syrian-factories-relocating-to-coastal-area|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author1=Stephanie Freid|title=Syrian civil war forces business owners to relocate|url=http://www.cctv-america.com/2015/01/05/syrian-civil-war-forces-business-owners-to-relocate|accessdate=2016-12-05|agency=CCTV America|date=2015-01-05|archive-date=2016-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160226034301/http://www.cctv-america.com/2015/01/05/syrian-civil-war-forces-business-owners-to-relocate|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

商业店铺受到的影响相对较小。在政府军控制下相对较安全的地区，各类商店正常运营，商业街的气氛和战前类似<ref name=airport/>。很多冲突区域的店主则迁到远离前线的地方，设立路边摊经商；原来的高档商店大多改建成了餐厅和面向战时需求的杂货店。由于燃料紧缺，城内还出现了出售柴薪、燃油和燃气的店铺<ref>{{cite news|author1=Edward Dark|title=Aleppo's war economy|url=http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2013/10/aleppo-war-economy-rebels-regime-syria.html|accessdate=2016-12-05|agency=Al-Monitor|date=2013-10-24|archive-date=2020-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200929052741/https://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2013/10/aleppo-war-economy-rebels-regime-syria.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2015年，阿勒颇的失业率达到19%，是内战前的两倍多<ref>{{cite web|author1=Karam Shaar|title=''Economy''|url=http://www.thealeppoproject.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Snapshot3Professions.docx-2.pdf|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-09-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200920151517/https://www.thealeppoproject.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Snapshot3Professions.docx-2.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。城内大米、糖、肉类等食品价格均比官方定价高出50%左右，而汽油、柴油和燃气价格可达官方价格的三倍<ref name="SEF"/>。

== 交通 ==
[[File:Aleppo_Bagdad_Railway_Station,_cropped.jpg|thumb]]
阿勒颇是叙利亚铁路枢纽，{{le|叙利亚铁路公司|Syrian Railways}}总部所在地。第一条经过阿勒颇的铁路线是{{le|巴格达铁路|Baghdad Railway}}，1912年阿勒颇段修建完成<ref name="Hughes">{{cite web|url=http://almashriq.hiof.no/lebanon/300/380/385/railways/resources/middleeast/|title=Middle East Railways|author=Hugh Hughes|publisher=almashriq.hiof.no|accessdate=2009-05-05|archive-date=2009-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090627164352/http://almashriq.hiof.no/lebanon/300/380/385/railways/resources/middleeast/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。这条铁路起初是为了方便两河流域的石油外运而建，后来因为叙利亚北部发达贸易的需求而修建了一条从阿勒颇出发去往叙利亚海岸的支线<ref> Earle, Edward Meade, ''Turkey, The Great Powers, and the Bagdad Railway.'' Russel and Russel 1966: 109-111.</ref>。至叙利亚内战前，铁路上还有开往土耳其和伊拉克的列车<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/middle_east/8518109.stm |title=BBC News: Iraq-Turkey railway link re-opens  |access-date=2016-11-03 |archive-date=2021-02-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210228044056/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/middle_east/8518109.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="wired-barry-2014">{{cite web|url=http://www.wired.com/2014/03/iraq-trains/|title=After Decades of War, Iraq Adds Fleet of New Trains to Its Aging Railway|last=Barry|first=Keith|date=March 24, 2014|publisher=Wired.com|accessdate=27 September 2015|archive-date=2021-03-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309204548/http://www.wired.com/2014/03/iraq-trains/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。阿勒颇还有通向[[大马士革|大马士革]]、[[拉塔基亚|拉塔基亚]]和[[代尔祖尔|代尔祖尔]]的三条标准轨距铁路<ref>{{cite web|author1=Ferenc Valoczy|title=CFS - Chemins de Fer Syriens|url=http://tuonela.tripod.com/syria/syria.html|accessdate=2016-11-21|archive-date=2020-09-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200917194944/http://tuonela.tripod.com/syria/syria.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。内战开始后，叙利亚北部铁路的轨道、站台、桥梁、车辆等损毁严重，列车常常成为恐怖袭击的目标。目前叙利亚北部铁路已经停运<ref>{{cite web|author1=Anne Barnard|title=Once Bustling, Syria’s Fractured Railroad Is a Testament to Shattered Ambitions|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/26/world/middleeast/damascus-syria-hejaz-railway-station.html?_r=0|publisher=New York Times|accessdate=2016-11-21|archive-date=2021-03-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309095050/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/26/world/middleeast/damascus-syria-hejaz-railway-station.html?_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[阿勒颇国际机场|阿勒颇国际机场]] （[[IATA|IATA]]: ALP, [[ICAO|ICAO]]: OSAP）是[[叙利亚航空|叙利亚航空]]的基地之一，于20世纪初建立。目前的航站楼在1999年开放<ref>Aleppo Int. Airport [http://www.terezia.org/section.php?id=1823 Historical Overview] {{Wayback|url=http://www.terezia.org/section.php?id=1823 |date=20171009230825 }}</ref>。2013年机场关闭，一年后重新开放<ref name=airport>[http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Middle-East/2014/Jan-22/244921-aleppo-airport-reopens-after-a-year-syria-state-media.ashx Aleppo airport reopens after a year: Syria state media] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Middle-East/2014/Jan-22/244921-aleppo-airport-reopens-after-a-year-syria-state-media.ashx |date=20141017154358 }}, The Daily Star, 22 January 2014</ref>。

